               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist and other saints; incipit of Text I; incipit of Text II and its subsections (fols. 4r, 13ra, 21rb, 21vb, 29ra, 38rb, 47vb, 65r, 74r, 83v-84r, 88rb, 90r); incipit of Text III and its subsections (fols. 92v, 96vb, 97va, 98rb, 99ra); incipit of Text IV and its subsections (fols. 100v, 101va, 101vb, 102ra, 102rb, 102va, 102vb, 103ra, 103va, 104ra, 104va, 105ra, 105va, 105vb, 106ra, 106rb, 106va, 106vb, 107ra);  elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the quire marks. &#xD;
&#xD;
A few groups of lines (alternating with black lines)on the incipit page of Texts I, II and III; a group of lines on the incipit page of Text IV.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The text of the Vita represents the first of the two sub-types of the Däbrä Libanos recension of the Gädlä Täklä Haymanot (close, but not identical to the published text of the Vita, s. E.A.W. BUDGE (ed., tr.), The Life and Miracles of Takla Hâymânôt in the Version of Dabra Lîbânôs..., London 1906).</note>
                     <note>- The miracles are apparently taken from different sets of miracles.</note>
                  </msItem>
