                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#108rb">Fol. 108rb</locus>: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 108rb: ዝመ{ጽ}ሐፍ፡ ዘወሀበቶ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ተክለ፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ዘቤት፡ ኖበይት፡ ወለተ፡ ብርሃን፡ ወብእሲሃ፡ ወልደ፡ መድኅን፡ ከመ፡ ይኩና፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፡ ወኢትርስዕዋ፡ ፩፩አቡነ፡ ዘበሰማያት፡ በጊዜ፡ አንበብክዎ፡ ደቂቀ፡ መቅደስ፡ ዓቢይ፡ ወንዑስ፤ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">Fol. 108rb: This is the book which Wälättä Bǝrhan and her husband Wäldä Mädḫǝn donated to ʾabunä Täklä Haymanot of Bet Nobäyt so that it might be for her the guide to the Kingdom of Heaven. Do not forget her (to recite for her) each of you, the Paternoster when you read it, children of the sanctuary, big and small. For ever and ever.</q>
                           The note is written in a recent, well-trained hand. The same hand added (partly rubricated) the names of the donor and her family members into the supplication formulas throughout the Ms. The note states that Wälättä Bǝrhan donated the Ms. to the church of ʾabunä Täklä Haymanot of Bet Nobäyt. Her husband, Wäldä Mädḫǝn, is also mentioned.
                        </item>
